{"title": "Fant\u00f4mas", "description": "<i>Fant\u00f4mas</i> is the first of 32 novels penned from 1911 to 1913 by Marcel Allain and Pierre Souvestre. The title character is a ruthless thief and killer, a bloodthirsty successor to LeBlanc's Ars\u00e8ne Lupin. The first five novels were made into silent film serials. The character and the movies caught the eye of the French Surrealists who admired the primal violence of Fant\u00f4mas, as well as his portrayal in the films, which are considered landmarks in French Cinema. In <i>Fant\u00f4mas</i>, the Marquise de Langrune is savagely murdered and Inspector Juve, who is obsessed with capturing Fant\u00f4mas, arrives to solve the murder. (Summary by Alan Winterrowd)", "duration": 36692, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "1100", "name": "Marcel Allain"}, {"id": "6316", "name": " Pierre Souvestre"}], "coverArt": "http://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt5/Fantomas_1007.jpg", "copyright_year": "1915", "genres": ["Detective Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Alan Winterrowd"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Alan Winterrowd"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Laurie Anne Walden"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Elli"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "01 - The Genius of Crime", "readers": [3483], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/fantomas_1007_librivox/fantomas_01_allain_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1400}, {"section": 2, "title": "02 - A Tragic Dawn", "readers": [3483], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/fantomas_1007_librivox/fantomas_02_allain_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1770}, {"section": 3, "title": "03 - The Hunt for the Man", "readers": [3483], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/fantomas_1007_librivox/fantomas_03_allain_64kb.mp3", "duration": 987}, {"section": 4, "title": "04 - 'No! I am not Mad!'", "readers": [3483], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/fantomas_1007_librivox/fantomas_04_allain_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1330}, {"section": 5, "title